library(RColorBrewer)
library(readxl)

#data cleaning

migration = read_excel("data/State_to_State_Migrations_Table_2018.xls",sheet = 1,skip=6)
## New names:
## * `` -> ...1
## * `` -> ...2
## * `` -> ...3
## * `` -> ...4
## * `` -> ...5
## * ...
migration = migration[complete.cases(migration), ]#remove NA rows
migration = migration[-1,]
states = migration$...1

df = migration[, (names(migration) %in% states)]#remain "estimates" columns
df[df=="N/A"]<-'0'#turn all Na values into 0
df = as.data.frame( lapply(df, as.numeric))
df1=cbind(states,df)#add state names to each row
#row names are the current locations
#people move from column states to row states

#pick sources

df2=select(df1,c("states","Texas","New.York","Virginia","North.Carolina"))
#build the three columns, source, target and count
df3=df2[,c(1,2)]
s1=c(rep("Texas",52))
df3=cbind(s1,df3)
colnames(df3)=c("source","target","count")

df4=df2[,c(1,3)]
s2=c(rep("New York",52))
df4=cbind(s2,df4)
colnames(df4)=c("source","target","count")

df5=df2[,c(1,4)]
s3=c(rep("Virginia",52))
df5=cbind(s3,df5)
colnames(df5)=c("source","target","count")

df6=df2[,c(1,5)]
s4=c(rep("North Carolina",52))
df6=cbind(s4,df6)
colnames(df6)=c("source","target","count")

df7=rbind(df3,df4,df5,df6)
#Pick the top 10 target states for each source state
df8=df7%>% group_by(source) %>%slice_max(order_by=count,n=10)
net <- graph_from_data_frame(d = df8, vertices = unique(c(df8$source, df8$target)), directed = T)


chordDiagram(df8, annotationTrack = "grid", preAllocateTracks = list(track.height = 0.1))
  circos.trackPlotRegion(track.index = 1, panel.fun = function(x, y) {
  col = rand_color(52,luminosity = "bright")
  xlim = get.cell.meta.data("xlim")
  xplot = get.cell.meta.data("xplot")
  ylim = get.cell.meta.data("ylim")
  sector.name = get.cell.meta.data("sector.index")
  circos.text(mean(xlim), ylim[1], sector.name, facing = "clockwise",
                niceFacing = TRUE, adj = c(0, 0.8), cex = 0.3)
}, bg.border = NA)
 
title("Mixed Migration in 2018",cex = 0.5)
